name: IVIMPOAntimicrobialMedications
title: IV, IM, PO Antimicrobial Medications
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains medications that are commonly used in an inpatient setting. These medications are not dose specific and include intravenous  (IV), intramuscular (IM ) or per os/by mouth (PO) antimicrobial medications that are either specifically mentioned in clinical practice guidelines or are reasonable therapeutic equivalents.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who are on antibiotic therapy. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Medication" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Use codes which represent only IV, IM, or PO antimicrobial medications.  Codes used are to be RxNorm codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.  The codes should be limited to those which are appropriate for human use and available to be prescribed in the United States. Drug forms that are not consistent with IV, IM, or PO administration should not be included. Drugs that take on topical or suppository forms should not be included.)
